The paper discusses the use of Deep Neural Networks (DNN) for wind power prediction, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on Deep Belief Networks (DBN) and their application in wind power prediction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves statistical analysis and regression, which could fall under cs.SD (Statistics and Data Analysis) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
